remixed_from.title: Reinforced Prusa X Carriage with Slim LM8UU Holder

description.text:
Fan add-on for this excellent carriage design. Utilises cheap and commonly available PCB fans - I found these on Fleabay for 95 cents each. I have been running with one of these fans without a shroud on my existing Mendel Prusa and will use one each end on the new printer I am building.
The holder does have screw pilot holes printed but I find my fan just presses in without the need for screws or glue. 28 September - added a shorter arm version that fits better on the x-carriages I have designed recently.

Print it and hang it off your x-carriage.
I'm using two of these, one each end.
3 perimeters, 3 layers, 0.35 nozzle, 0.25mm layer height, 25% infill at 90 degrees fill angle.

comments.text: On my MendelMax, there is only 41mm between the two smooth rods in the X-drive. I sanded 1.5 mm of each of the two upper corners.

title: Landing skids with Battery holder for Hovership quad

description.text:
Made some custom legs for the Hovership quad: http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:251002 The lower COG might not help with aerobatics so I wouldn't recommend this mounting set up if that's what you're going after. This position might be better suited for video recording to stabilize the quad. Flight tests are coming soon. It is made for a Zippy Compact 2200 3S battery. It measures approx. 107mm x 35mm x 21mm. There are two versions, one with an end stop and one without. I have one of each version installed in the pictures. The small groove on the bottom is for a velcro strap. It's about 1/2" wide or 13mm. I plan on designing a bar that goes along the bottom that attaches to both pairs of landing skids. I originally designed it with the bar built in but printing it would be tough. UPDATE 4-7-2014:
I made a new set of legs + a bar that connects the two together. See the new models that were uploaded.

remixed_from.title: Greg's Hinged Accessible Extruder With New Motor Mount

title: Greg's Hinged Accessible Extruder With Extrusion Base Mount Designed for Bowden

description.text:
I have been using a Greg's Wade extruder on my printer for over 3 years. I wanted to design a base mount that could work with 1515 and 2020 extrusions for delta printers. I liked Joachim Sturm's updates to the motor mount screws so I started wit his, and added a Bowed_mount hotend type and customized the Base. I'm not sure if any of the other mounts will work now.  
I ahve included all of the scad files you would need to customize this. I may go in and clean up the code, but not likely ;)

Same as any Wades. The base is designed for 3mm x 20mm length screws. It's also designed for SMC KQ2H06-02AS Brass Push-to-Connect Tube Fitting with Sealant, Adapter, 6 mm Tube OD x 1/4" BSPT Male. Just adjust the extruder_recess_d in the Bowden_mount function to match yours.
